Apparently we use ReactDOMServer.renderToStaticNodeStream() somehow which is deprecated and causes quite a lot of warnings in the website logs:
Warning: ReactDOMServer.renderToStaticNodeStream() is deprecated.  \
Use ReactDOMServer.renderToPipeableStream() and wait to `pipe` until the `onAllReady` callback has been called instead.

It's quite likely this is part of server side rendering and hence needs to be fixed in one of our dependencies, but might be good to quickly look into (and possibly report upstream). If we get annoyed by the warnings, we might be able to silence them somehow or downgrade React for now.
