Currently, for seq details to work, we require all lapis instances to work, not just the one whose sequence details we want to look up.
This is because we query all instances, not just the first to return successfully: 


      loculus/website/src/pages/seq/[accessionVersion]/findOrganismAndData.ts


        Lines 9 to 14
      in
      d62c6ef







           const promises = organisms.map(async ({ key }) => { 




               return { 




                   organism: key, 




                   result: await getSequenceDetailsTableData(accessionVersion, key), 




               }; 




           }); 





We can probably change this to only require one of the requests to succeed in finding the correct organism - this could also speed up the endpoint to not require all lapis endpoints to return: we know that every accession can only exist in one instance, so we might as well use the first one that finds it.

