{
"name": "Pathoplexus backend",
"status": "Healthy",
"documentation": "visit /swagger-ui/index.html"
}

Our express server proxies to the backend and lapis. In #488 we thought about introducing a proxy for keycloak (which we did not do), but, during development we came across setting the forward headers. So we should think about introducing them for our backend and lapis proxy.
        onProxyReq: (proxyReq, req) => {
            proxyReq.setHeader('X-Forwarded-For', req.ip);
            proxyReq.setHeader('X-Forwarded-Port', req.connection.remotePort);
            proxyReq.setHeader('X-Forwarded-*', 'true');
            proxyReq.setHeader('Forwarded', `for=${req.ip};host=${req.headers.host};proto=${req.protocol}`);
            proxyReq.setHeader('X-Forwarded', `${req.protocol} for=${req.ip};host=${req.headers.host}`);
            proxyReq.setHeader('X-Forwarded-Host', req.headers.host);
            proxyReq.setHeader('X-Forwarded-Proto', req.protocol);
        }

